  "management45": "Critical operational constraints are flagged at 5 airports right now. No engine anti-ice operations are currently flagged. Across base airports: 2 critical, 13 high, 10 medium, 14 normal. Key bases needing attention include London Luton (LTN/EGGW), Copernicus Wrocław (WRO/EPWR) and Katowice Wojciech Korfanty (KTW/EPKT); plus 12 other bases. 10 additional base airports are at medium severity and should be monitored closely. At base airports, the dominant pattern is fog / freezing fog, mist and very low visibility  — most notably around London Luton (LTN/EGGW), Katowice Wojciech Korfanty (KTW/EPKT) and Copernicus Wrocław (WRO/EPWR). Network hotspots: London Luton (LTN/EGGW), Katowice Wojciech Korfanty (KTW/EPKT), Keflavik (KEF/BIKF), Lisbon Humberto Delgado (LIS/LPPT), Almaty (ALA/UAAA). Primary drivers: very low visibility, mist and approach minima limits. Expected impact is reduced runway capacity with higher delay and diversion risk, especially where visibility/RVR and cloud base are very low. Since the last update, 2 airports changed status, led by Copenhagen Kastrup (CPH/EKCH), Beauvais Tillé (BVA/LFOB).",
